<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="535" pageId="5" pageNumber="534" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1906,2025]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,131,293]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="535" pageId="5" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1928,1953]" pageId="5" pageNumber="534">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The gonostylus, which is broader than long, has an unusually large pectinate claw (
<figureCitation box="[1247,1339,1928,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="534">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
, ↓1), but whether the claw is interrupted in the middle, or continuous and just depressed, is not clear. The gonocoxal emargination, whose outline is almost circular, is occupied by the aedeagal bulge, which has numerous, sclerotized hooks of various sizes ventrally and a pair of larger, pointed teeth laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1119,154,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
, ↓2). The medial gonocoxal bridges are provided with glabrous, slender processes that protrude beyond the posterior gonocoxal edge (
<figureCitation box="[1344,1431,190,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
, ↓3). The tegmen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2018" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[373,546,230,253]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pahangensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[373,546,230,253]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">B. paHangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose basic structure resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[1019,1165,229,253]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[1019,1165,229,253]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">B. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is unique in having an angular-shaped cap at the apex and a pair of finger-shaped processes dorsosubapically (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1219,268,293]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
, ↓4).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" startId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" targetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1687,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1687,1709]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Male morphology of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2018" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[512,774,1687,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pahangensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[512,774,1687,1709]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Bernadottea pahangenSiS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(holotype). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[904,931,1687,1708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">A:</emphasis>
Gonostylus, dorsal. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1149,1175,1688,1709]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">B:</emphasis>
Ninth tergite, dorsal. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1409,1436,1687,1709]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">C:</emphasis>
Genitalia, ventral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[339,365,1719,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">D:</emphasis>
Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[808,833,1719,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">E:</emphasis>
Fourth flagellomere, lateral. Scales 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1779,2023]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,415,1779,1804]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Other characters.</emphasis>
Body size 
<quantity box="[552,645,1780,1804]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="535" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[660,731,1779,1804]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Head.</emphasis>
Eye bridge 2–3 ommatidia long dorsally. Flagellomeres 10; apical flagellomere long, composed of two bodies; neck of fourth flagellomere 0.7 times as long as node (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1424,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,222,1851,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Wing.</emphasis>
R1 = 4 times Rs. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,547,1851,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergal setae situated laterally; pleural membrane of anterior segments asetose, of posterior segments with single setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[603,720,1890,1915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Ninth tergite with wide, shallow emargination posteriorly (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites: ventral portions extensively, darkly pigmented around emargination and along longitudinal axis, broadly rounded posteriorly; dorsal apodemes long, protruding beyond ventroanterior gonocoxal edge (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,1962,1987]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,363,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,327,1666]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male morphology of Bernadottea pahangenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175084/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="535">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct broadly rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
